  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "PruIHRIziqvqQIfnIbdSoHmmIk8=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:42.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Decision\n\nConnect's live collaboration does **not** use a CRDT. The reactor's existing operation-based document model already resolves concurrent edits: each user produces an independent stream of ops, and `reactor.load()` applies remote ops with proper ordering via skip/noop/merge semantics.\n\n## Why this works\n\n- Ops are signed and attributed to their author, so provenance is preserved across peers.\n- Each peer's feed is append-only and per-user, so there is no shared write cursor to contest.\n- Reordering and merge semantics live in the document model, not in the transport \u2014 SwarmChannel only has to pull new batches and hand them to the reactor.\n\n## UX consequence\n\nBecause Powerhouse editors are too varied (tables, visual canvases, dashboards, button grids) to support meaningful per-editor cursors, the **only live surface is the document toolbar's History view**: peers' ops appear there in real time, attributed to the correct signer. No per-editor presence, no collaborative cursors.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:42.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:42.000Z"
    }
  },
